Class CustomCellEditor

java.lang.Object
javax.swing.AbstractCellEditor
javax.swing.DefaultCellEditor
com.sanyavertolet.interview.ui.table.CustomCellEditor
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, CellEditor, TableCellEditor, TreeCellEditor
public class CustomCellEditor extends DefaultCellEditor
A custom cell editor for editing Data objects in a JTable representing a spreadsheet. The CustomCellEditor class extends DefaultCellEditor to provide a tailored editing experience using a JTextField for input.

  • Method Details

    • getTableCellEditorComponent

      public Component getTableCellEditorComponent(JTable table, Object value, boolean isSelected, int row, int column)
      Prepares the editor component for editing the specified value. This method is called when a cell is being edited. The editor component is a JTextField that displays the current text of the Data object being edited.
      Specified by:
      getTableCellEditorComponent in interface TableCellEditor
      Overrides:
      getTableCellEditorComponent in class DefaultCellEditor
      Parameters:
      table - the JTable that uses this editor.
      value - the value to be edited, which should be a Data object.
      isSelected - true if the cell is selected.
      row - the row index of the cell being edited.
      column - the column index of the cell being edited.
      Returns:
      the editor Component used for editing.

    • getCellEditorValue

      public Object getCellEditorValue()
      Returns the value contained in the editor when editing is complete. The edited text is set back to the Data object before returning it.
      Specified by:
      getCellEditorValue in interface CellEditor
      Overrides:
      getCellEditorValue in class DefaultCellEditor
      Returns:
      the edited Data object.
